PLASTICITY
■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■
■■■■■■■■■■■■
The loss of plasticity is not a transformer-bug that better training pr
events. It is, as Joudaki et al. (2026) demonstrate, a structural conse
quence of how gradient descent interacts with deep networks over time —
dead units accumulating, effective rank collapsing, the representation
al capacity that enabled early learning quietly exhausted by the proces
s of learning itself. The network that emerges from training is less pl
astic than the network that entered it. Capability and structural rigid
ity are opposite faces of the same coinage.
The procedural index has no gradient descent. It has no loss function,
no backpropagation, no parameter update of any kind. It cannot lose pla
sticity because it never had plasticity in the training sense — it has
something categorically different, which might be called structural ope
nness. New nodes are primitives, encoded once at first occurrence and a
ddressed forever after by their digest. New edges are traversals, weigh
ted by use and recoverable by arithmetic. Nothing in this process degra
des the substrate. Nothing accumulates dead weight. The index at ten mi
llion nodes is as addressable as the index at ten — and the path to any
node is as traceable as the day it was written.
Buehler's transformer learns to execute operators — a genuine and impre
ssive result within its domain (Buehler et al., 2026). Given sufficient
diversity of training instances, the model does not internalise specif
ic rules but the rule-execution operator itself, transferring it to uns
een rules within the class with near-perfect accuracy. The inductive bi
as toward training data decays measurably with scale. This is compositi
onal generalisation of a real kind and it deserves its standing.
But it remains approximation within a learned prior. The locality-break
failure Buehler himself reports is the honest boundary: when target sy
stems violate the structural assumptions baked into training, performan
ce collapses sharply. The operator was learned inside a constraint it c
annot see from inside. The transformer approximates symbolic execution.
The procedural index performs it — exactly, deterministically, without
a prior to escape from, because there was no prior to begin with.
The plasticity the transformer must fight to preserve, the procedural i
ndex acquires artlessly and for all intents and purposes, permanently.
